# Local Configuration (CLAUDE.local.md)

This file contains instructions specific to your local environment.
Copy this file to `CLAUDE.local.md` and customize it.

## Development Environment

### Environment Variables
- DATABASE_URL: [your local DB connection]
- API_KEY: [your dev API key]

### Ports Used
- Frontend: http://localhost:3000
- Backend: http://localhost:8080
- Database: localhost:5432

## Personal Preferences

### Code Style
- I prefer arrow functions
- I use tabs / spaces (2/4)
- I prefer async/await over Promises

### Local Tools
- Editor: VS Code / Vim / WebStorm
- Terminal: iTerm2 / Terminal / Windows Terminal
- Node version: v20.x

## Additional Context

### Tasks in Progress
- [ ] Feature X under development on branch feature/x
- [ ] Bug Y to investigate

### Important Notes
- Service Z is sometimes unstable locally
- Use `npm run dev:mock` to avoid real API calls

## Frequent Local Commands

```bash
# Start the entire environment
docker-compose up -d

# Real-time logs
docker-compose logs -f

# Reset the local DB
npm run db:reset

# Seed with test data
npm run db:seed
```

## Do Not Do on This Machine

- IMPORTANT: Do not run load tests
- IMPORTANT: Do not modify files in /config/prod/
